Vol / Page:  1/4
Edition:
Quote:  An act to amend the Reserve Bank of NZ Act, 1933. <i>Ibid.</i> 1/7 It shall be the general function of the Reserve Bank.. to give effect as far as may be to the monetary policy of the Government, as communicated to it from time to time by the Minister of Finance... The bank shall regulate and control credit and currency in New Zealand, the transfer of moneys to or from New Zealand, and the disposal of moneys that were derived from the sale of any New Zealand products and for the time being are held overseas.
